    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>+ Nos <persName key="#Princeps" ref="#people/3010">secundus
                            Riccardus</persName>, divina ordinante clementia <placeName
                            key="#Cities" ref="#places/173">Capuanorum</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Princeps">princeps</rs>, patefacimus universis fidelibus nostris
                        quam, per <rs key="#Intercessory">interventu</rs>
                        <persName key="#Intercessory #Witness #childOf" ref="#people/3079">Rainaldi
                            cognomine Muscae</persName>, <persName><name ref="Turaldus"
                                >Turoldi</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#childOf">fìlii</rs>, pro animabus principum <persName
                            key="#Princeps #grandparentOf" ref="#people/3001">Riccardi</persName>
                        <rs key="#grandparentOf">avi</rs> et <persName key="#Princeps #parentOf"
                            ref="#people/3002">Iordani</persName>
                        <rs key="#parentOf">patris</rs> nostri, et ob statum nostri principatus,
                        concessimus et confirmavimus tibi donum quod, ob redemptionem animae patris
                        et matris meae, fecit <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterio</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Immunity #Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/3000">Sancti
                            Laurentii</orgName>, prope <rs key="#Walls">muros</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/4000">Aversae</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Cities">urbis</rs> sito, et domino <persName
                            key="#Abbots #Personal_rank" ref="#people/3016">Guarino</persName>
                        <rs key="#Personal_rank">venerabili</rs>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abbati</rs>, eiusque successoribus atque custodibus,
                        videlicet <rs
                            key="#Casalia #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure"
                            >casalem</rs> qui dicitur <placeName ref="#places/4029"
                            key="#Casalia #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure"
                                ><geogName
                                key="#Casalia #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure"
                                ref="#estates/3016">Nolitum</geogName></placeName>, cum omnibus eius
                        appenditiis, qualiter ipse prefatus Rainaldus in suo dominio tenebat,
                        acceptis tamen ab eodem inde <rs key="#Value #Gift">quadringentis
                            solidis</rs> et una <rs key="#Clothings #Gift">cappella</rs> pro
                            benedictione;<rs key="#Immunity"> remota omni contrarietate et
                            molestatione principum successorum nostrorum vel vice principum, comitum
                            vel vice comitum, iudicum, sculdaorum, castaldeorum, aliorumque omnium
                            mortalium personae</rs>. Quod si quis huius nostrae concessionis et
                        confirmationis contemptor aut violator esse tentaverit, <rs key="#Penalty"
                            >centum libras auri purissimi</rs> persolvat, medietatem nostro sacro
                        palatio, et medietatem praefato monasterio et domino praescripto Guarino
                        venerabili abbati, eiusque successoribus atque custodibus. Solutaque poena
                        librarum, haec nostra concessio et confirmatio firma, munita atque
                        inviolabilis maneat in perpetuum. Et ut hoc firmius credatur, et diligentius
                        ab omnibus observetur, manu propria nostra subscripsimus, et nostri sigilli
                        impressione iussimus insigniri. (M). + Signum <persName
                            key="#Intercessory #Witness #childOf" ref="#people/3079">Rainaldi
                            Muscae</persName>. + Signum <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Radulfus de Miczegros">Rodulfi de Mucengros</name></persName>.
                        + Signum <persName key="#Witness #Viscount" ref="#people/3078"
                            >Stantionis</persName>
                        <rs key="#Viscount">vice comitis</rs>. + Signum <persName key="#Witness"
                                ><name ref="Turstainus Troglet">Turstayni Troglet</name></persName>.
                        + Signum <persName key="#Witness" ref="#people/3080">Rainaldi
                            Lopini</persName>. + Signum <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Rainfredus Sorellus">Rainfridi Sorelli</name></persName>. +
                        Signum <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Wido de Doeli">Iconis de
                                Doeli</name></persName>. Ex iussione praefatae serenissimae
                        potestatis, scripsi ego <persName key="#Writer #Judge" ref="#people/3012"
                            >Quiriacus </persName><rs key="#Judge">iudex</rs>, in anno Dominicae
                        incarnationis millesimo nonagesimo quarto, et .XIV. principatus ipsius
                        domini Riccardi gloriosi principis. Datum <placeName key="#Cities"
                            ref="#places/4000">Aversae</placeName>, mense aprili, per indictionem
                        .II.</ab>
